ZH: 在高速公路上，有时候一些车道会被封闭。
EN: Sometimes, lanes on the highway are closed off.

ZH: 在这座城市里，车道总是拥挤不堪。
EN: Lanes in this city are always congested.

ZH: 车道上的标线应该清晰可见。
EN: Lane markings on the road should be visible.

ZH: 这条车道只允许汽车通行。
EN: This lane is for cars only.

ZH: 紧急救援车辆可以使用应急车道。
EN: Emergency vehicles can use the emergency lane.

ZH: 不要驶入对向车道。
EN: Do not drive into oncoming lanes.

ZH: 前方车道有交通堵塞。
EN: There is traffic congestion in the lane ahead.

ZH: 驾驶员应该时刻留意侧边的车道。
EN: Drivers should always be aware of the lanes on the side.

ZH: 这条车道正在施工中，暂时关闭。
EN: This lane is under construction and temporarily closed.

ZH: 改道前请先打开转向灯。
EN: Turn on the turn signal before changing lanes.

ZH: 这条高速车道速度限制是120公里每小时。
EN: The speed limit on this highway lane is 120 kilometers per hour.

ZH: 他违规一直使用应急车道。
EN: He kept using the emergency lane in violation of the rules.

ZH: 这条车道只允许超车。
EN: This lane is designated for overtaking.

ZH: 请保持在车道中间行驶。
EN: Please keep driving in the middle of the lane.

ZH: 车辆必须保持在指定车道内行驶。
EN: Vehicles must travel within designated lanes.

ZH: 他沿着车道飞驰而过。
EN: He sped along the lane.

ZH: 这段路上有几条车道可供选择。
EN: There are several lanes to choose from on this road.

ZH: 车辆不得逆向驶入车道。
EN: Vehicles are not allowed to enter lanes in the opposite direction.

ZH: 她用车道标志指引着方向。
EN: She used lane markings to guide her direction.

ZH: 出租车中的乘客有时候会吐在车道上。
EN: Passengers in taxis sometimes vomit on the lanes.
